glosses: To rise, to move up in height.
To move up in level, rank or title.

etymology: From Ottoman Turkish یوكسلمك (yükselmek, “to rise, to mount”), from Proto-Turkic *yükse- (“to rise”), from Proto-Turkic *yük- (“upwards”), morphologically yükse- (obsolete) + -l- + -mek. The passive form has replaced the base form and the passive suffix has lost its function.
